Looking at your codebase, here's a thorough analysis of the tab opportunity and potential additions.

## Status Bar Tabs — TC2000 Style

The current status bar (`kite/widgets/status_bar.py`) is a single thin ribbon showing Market/API/Heartbeat. TC2000 uses tabs at the bottom to switch between contextual data panels without losing chart real estate.

### How It Would Work

The tab bar would sit just above the status ribbon. Clicking a tab slides a collapsible panel up (like a drawer) — the chart stays full size, the panel overlays the bottom ~25-30% like a terminal tray. Pressing the same tab again collapses it. This is the same pattern ThinkorSwim and Bloomberg use for their bottom panels.

