## Additional Dialogs Worth Adding for Swing Trading

**High priority:**

- **Risk Calculator Dialog** — Input: entry price, stop price, account size → outputs position size, max shares, R-multiple target. TC2000 has this built into the order dialog. Integrates with your `OrderDialog` as a side panel.

- **Trade Journal Entry Dialog** — After an order fills, a lightweight popup: setup type dropdown (Momentum Breakout / EP / Parabolic / Base / etc.), grade (A/B/C), notes field. Saves to SQLite alongside the trade. Feeds performance analytics by setup type.

- **Symbol Overview Panel** — Expands your existing `StockInfoDialog` to add a price history sparkline, sector relative strength vs NIFTY, and 52-week percentile rank. Accessible via right-click on any symbol anywhere in the app.

- **Multi-Chart Layout Dialog** — A 2x2 or 1x3 grid of the same `CandlestickChart` widget for different symbols or timeframes. Your chart engine is already component-based so this is clean to implement.

**Medium priority:**

- **Screener Builder Dialog** — Visual drag-and-drop Chartink clause builder. Dropdown for condition type, parameter spinboxes, preview of clause string, save to named scan. Replaces the raw text entry in `ModernAddScanDialog`.

- **Position Sizing Wizard** — Multi-step: (1) enter setup details, (2) mark entry/stop on a mini chart, (3) review calculated size and R targets, (4) confirm sends directly to `OrderDialog`. Enforces discipline around sizing.

- **Daily Review Dialog** — End-of-day summary: all trades with chart thumbnails (canvas snapshot via `snapshot_btn`), P&L by setup type, win rate, notes. Exportable to PDF.

