## Implementation Note for the Tab Bar

The cleanest implementation is a `QTabBar` (not `QTabWidget` — you don't want the frame) with `setDrawBase(False)` sitting in a `QWidget` that animates height between 0 and ~220px using `QPropertyAnimation`. Each tab maps to a stacked widget panel. The animation should respect the splitter so the chart panel shrinks rather than being overlapped — set `setMaximumHeight` on the chart container and animate that alongside the drawer height.

The tab bar itself should live between the main splitter and the status ribbon, inheriting the `#070a0f` background with `1px solid #1a2030` borders matching your existing dialog spec.